Paul Krendler's over here from Justice.

748
01:01:06,914 --> 01:01:09,584
She's asking him to take over in Memphis.

749
01:01:34,358 --> 01:01:36,110
Welcome to Memphis, Dr. Lecter.

750
01:01:36,277 --> 01:01:38,988
I'm Lieutenant Boyle.
This is Sergeant Patrick.

751
01:01:39,155 --> 01:01:41,199
Now, we're gonna treat you
as good as you treat us.

752
01:01:41,365 --> 01:01:44,827
You be a gentleman,
you gonna get three hots and a cot.

753
01:01:45,578 --> 01:01:49,040
Sir. If you sign right here,
we'll have us a legal transfer.

754
01:01:52,126 --> 01:01:53,544
Where is it?

755
01:01:54,795 --> 01:01:56,589
Here, sir. Use mine.

756
01:02:43,636 --> 01:02:47,515
Senator Martin, Dr. Hannibal Lecter.

757
01:02:52,812 --> 01:02:54,230
Dr. Lecter,

758
01:02:54,897 --> 01:02:58,234
I brought an affidavit
guaranteeing your new rights.

759
01:02:58,567 --> 01:03:01,195
You'll want to read it before I sign.

760
01:03:04,740 --> 01:03:09,120
I won't waste your time or Catherine's
time bargaining for petty privileges.

761
01:03:09,287 --> 01:03:11,289
Clarice Starling
and that awful Jack Crawford

762
01:03:11,455 --> 01:03:13,499
have wasted far too much time already.

763
01:03:13,666 --> 01:03:16,627
I only pray they haven't doomed
the poor girl.

764
01:03:17,753 --> 01:03:21,340
Let me help you now
and I will trust you when it is all over.

765
01:03:21,507 --> 01:03:23,384
You have my word. Paul?

766
01:03:25,886 --> 01:03:28,723
Buffalo Bill's real name is Louis Friend.

767
01:03:29,974 --> 01:03:31,017
I met him just once.

768
01:03:31,183 --> 01:03:34,145
He was referred to me in April
or May, 1980,

769
01:03:34,312 --> 01:03:36,605
by my patient Benjamin Raspail.

770
01:03:37,148 --> 01:03:39,191
They were lovers, you see.

771
01:03:39,358 --> 01:03:42,820
But Raspail had become very frightened.

772
01:03:43,612 --> 01:03:46,824
Apparently, Louis had murdered a transient

773
01:03:47,241 --> 01:03:50,328
and done things with her skin.

774
01:03:51,370 --> 01:03:54,498
We need his address
and a physical description.

775
01:03:55,499 --> 01:03:57,168
Tell me, Senator.

776
01:03:57,793 --> 01:04:00,212
Did you nurse Catherine yourself?

777
01:04:00,671 --> 01:04:02,965
- What?
- Did you breast-feed her?

778
01:04:03,090 --> 01:04:05,676
- Now, wait a minute!
- Yes, I did.

779
01:04:06,135 --> 01:04:09,764
- Toughened your nipples, didn't it?
- You son of a bitch!

780
01:04:10,014 --> 01:04:13,559
Amputate a man's leg,
and he can still feel it tickling.

781
01:04:13,976 --> 01:04:17,438
Tell me, Mom,
when your little girl is on the slab,

782
01:04:17,605 --> 01:04:19,482
where will it tickle you?

783
01:04:19,648 --> 01:04:22,568
Take this thing back to Baltimore.

784
01:04:24,111 --> 01:04:27,198
Five-foot-ten, strongly built,
about 180 pounds.

785
01:04:27,365 --> 01:04:29,575
Hair, blond. Eyes, pale blue.

786
01:04:30,076 --> 01:04:31,327
He'd be about 35 now.

787
01:04:31,494 --> 01:04:34,497
He said he lived in Philadelphia,
but may have lied.

788
01:04:34,663 --> 01:04:36,540
That's all I can remember, Mom.

789
01:04:36,707 --> 01:04:39,794
But if I think of any more,
I will let you know.

790
01:04:41,837 --> 01:04:44,256
Oh, and, Senator, just one more thing.

791
01:04:46,592 --> 01:04:48,177
Love your suit.

792
01:04:50,388 --> 01:04:52,556
I tell you now
that in a meeting earlier this evening

793
01:04:52,723 --> 01:04:53,891
with Senator Ruth Martin,

794
01:04:54,058 --> 01:04:56,977
{\an8}Dr. Lecter agreed
to assist in the investigation

795
01:04:57,144 --> 01:04:59,897
{\an8}of trying to find the abductor
of Catherine Martin, Buffalo Bill.

796
01:05:00,064 --> 01:05:01,023
How do you fit in, sir?

797
01:05:01,190 --> 01:05:02,751
Well, it's only through
my own unique insight

798
01:05:02,775 --> 01:05:04,836
into Lecter's mind
that this breakthrough was possible.

799
01:05:04,860 --> 01:05:06,004
And Buffalo Bill's real name...

800
01:05:06,028 --> 01:05:09,824
Buffalo Bill's real name is now a matter
of record with the proper authorities.

801
01:05:09,990 --> 01:05:12,677
- Can you give us any more information?
- My name is Dr. Frederick Chilton.

802
01:05:12,701 --> 01:05:14,120
- How do you spell that?
- C-H...

803
01:05:15,746 --> 01:05:20,292
- Are you with Dr. Chilton's group?
- Oh, well, I just saw him outside, sir.

804
01:05:20,668 --> 01:05:24,046
Access to Lecter is strictly limited.
We've been getting death threats.

805
01:05:24,213 --> 01:05:25,881
I understand, sir.

806
01:05:31,929 --> 01:05:34,014
Log in. Check your weapon.

807
01:05:34,849 --> 01:05:37,184
Well,
I can't take all the credit for myself.

808
01:05:37,351 --> 01:05:39,854
Senator Martin, the Justice Department,
the people at the FBI,

809
01:05:39,979 --> 01:05:42,106
the folks at the Baltimore State Hospital.

810
01:05:42,273 --> 01:05:45,568
And now for the hard part,
apprehending the suspect.

811
01:05:45,776 --> 01:05:48,279
Excuse me, folks,
I'm gonna have to catch a flight.

812
01:05:52,158 --> 01:05:54,410
Command desk. Officer Jacobs.

813
01:06:03,002 --> 01:06:05,129
Is it true what they're saying?

814
01:06:07,214 --> 01:06:09,300
He's some kind of vampire?

815
01:06:11,635 --> 01:06:14,305
They don't have a name for what he is.

816
01:06:14,972 --> 01:06:16,807
You do know the rules, ma'am?

817
01:06:17,308 --> 01:06:19,935
Yes, Lieutenant Boyle.
I've questioned him before.

818
01:06:23,272 --> 01:06:24,565
Go ahead.

819
01:07:01,477 --> 01:07:03,354
Good evening, Clarice.

820
01:07:05,022 --> 01:07:08,359
I thought you might like
your drawings back, Doctor.

821
01:07:10,486 --> 01:07:12,696
Just until you get your view.

822
01:07:13,197 --> 01:07:15,032
How very thoughtful.

823
01:07:16,408 --> 01:07:19,495
Or did Jack Crawford send you
for one last wheedle

824
01:07:19,662 --> 01:07:21,830
before you're both booted off the case?

825
01:07:22,206 --> 01:07:24,542
No. I came because I wanted to.

826
01:07:29,129 --> 01:07:31,382
People will say we're in love.

827
01:07:35,678 --> 01:07:37,721
Anthrax Island.

828
01:07:38,389 --> 01:07:41,350
That was an especially nice touch,
Clarice.

829
01:07:41,559 --> 01:07:43,852
- Yours?
- Yes.

830
01:07:44,728 --> 01:07:47,898
Yeah! That was good.

831
01:07:48,774 --> 01:07:50,818
Pity about poor Catherine, though.

832
01:07:53,362 --> 01:07:55,823
Your anagrams are showing, Doctor.

833
01:07:56,740 --> 01:07:58,242
Louis Friend?

834
01:07:58,951 --> 01:08:01,912
Iron sulfide, also known as Fool's Gold.

835
01:08:02,580 --> 01:08:06,667
Oh, Clarice. Your problem is
you need to get more fun out of life.

836
01:08:06,917 --> 01:08:09,878
You were telling me the truth
back in Baltimore, sir.

837
01:08:10,004 --> 01:08:11,755
Please continue now.

838
01:08:12,089 --> 01:08:14,925
Well, I have read the case files,
have you?

839
01:08:15,092 --> 01:08:18,178
Everything you need to find him
is right there in those pages.

840
01:08:18,345 --> 01:08:22,725
- Then tell me how.
- First principles, Clarice. Simplicity.

841
01:08:23,267 --> 01:08:24,727
Read Marcus Aurelius.

842
01:08:24,893 --> 01:08:28,105
Of each particular thing,
ask what is it in itself?

843
01:08:28,314 --> 01:08:30,107
What is its nature?

844
01:08:30,566 --> 01:08:33,819
What does he do, this man you seek?

845
01:08:36,030 --> 01:08:37,531
He kills women.

846
01:08:37,698 --> 01:08:40,159
No! That is incidental.

847
01:08:41,327 --> 01:08:43,127
What is the first
and principal thing he does?

848
01:08:43,287 --> 01:08:46,498
What needs does he serve by killing?

849
01:08:47,041 --> 01:08:48,250
Anger.

850
01:08:49,960 --> 01:08:54,256
Social acceptance
and sexual frustrations...

851
01:08:54,423 --> 01:08:57,301
No! He covets.

852
01:08:58,636 --> 01:09:00,387
That is his nature.

853
01:09:00,721 --> 01:09:03,349
And how do we begin to covet, Clarice?

854
01:09:03,849 --> 01:09:06,185
Do we seek out things to covet?

855
01:09:07,019 --> 01:09:09,021
Make an effort to answer now.

856
01:09:09,188 --> 01:09:11,440
No. We just...

857
01:09:11,857 --> 01:09:14,985
No. We begin by coveting
what we see every day.

858
01:09:15,319 --> 01:09:18,614
Don't you feel eyes
moving over your body, Clarice?

859
01:09:19,490 --> 01:09:22,660
And don't your eyes
seek out the things you want?

860
01:09:23,410 --> 01:09:25,829
All right. Yes. Now please tell me how.

861
01:09:26,205 --> 01:09:30,084
No. It is your turn to tell me, Clarice.

862
01:09:30,334 --> 01:09:33,170
You don't have any more vacations to sell.

863
01:09:33,545 --> 01:09:35,798
Why did you leave that ranch?

864
01:09:36,340 --> 01:09:40,010
Doctor, we don't have any more time
for any of this now.

865
01:09:40,511 --> 01:09:43,138
But we don't reckon time the same way,
do we, Clarice?

866
01:09:43,305 --> 01:09:45,140
This is all the time you'll ever have.

867
01:09:45,307 --> 01:09:47,685
Later. Now, please, listen to me.
We've only got five...

868
01:09:47,851 --> 01:09:50,354
No! I will listen now.

869
01:09:53,357 --> 01:09:55,192
After your father's murder,
you were orphaned.

870
01:09:55,359 --> 01:09:56,485
You were ten years old.

871
01:09:56,652 --> 01:10:00,364
You went to live with cousins
on a sheep and horse ranch in Montana.

872
01:10:00,531 --> 01:10:01,573
And?

873
01:10:03,701 --> 01:10:05,869
And one morning, I just ran away.

874
01:10:06,578 --> 01:10:09,665
Not "just", Clarice. What set you off?

875
01:10:10,416 --> 01:10:13,877
- You started at what time?
- Early. Still dark.

876
01:10:14,211 --> 01:10:18,215
Then something woke you, didn't it?
Was it a dream? What was it?

877
01:10:19,591 --> 01:10:21,593
I heard a strange noise.

878
01:10:22,553 --> 01:10:23,971
What was it?

879
01:10:24,555 --> 01:10:28,058
It was screaming.

880
01:10:29,977 --> 01:10:32,938
Some kind of screaming,
like a child's voice.

881
01:10:33,355 --> 01:10:34,940
What did you do?

882
01:10:35,357 --> 01:10:38,902
I went downstairs, outside.

883
01:10:41,739 --> 01:10:43,741
I crept up into the barn.

884
01:10:44,491 --> 01:10:47,536
I was so scared to look inside,
but I had to.

885
01:10:48,746 --> 01:10:51,874
And what did you see, Clarice?
What did you see?

886
01:10:53,584 --> 01:10:57,171
Lambs. They were screaming.

887
01:10:58,297 --> 01:11:01,091
They were slaughtering the spring lambs?

888
01:11:01,467 --> 01:11:03,469
And they were screaming.

889
01:11:04,720 --> 01:11:07,222
- And you ran away?
- No.

890
01:11:08,432 --> 01:11:10,559
First I tried to free them.

891
01:11:11,101 --> 01:11:13,520
I opened the gate to their pen,
but they wouldn't run.

892
01:11:13,645 --> 01:11:16,940
They just stood there, confused.
They wouldn't run.

893
01:11:17,316 --> 01:11:19,985
But you could and you did, didn't you?

894
01:11:20,694 --> 01:11:24,156
Yes. I took one lamb,
and I ran away as fast as I could.

895
01:11:24,323 --> 01:11:26,825
- Where were you going, Clarice?
- I don't know.

896
01:11:26,992 --> 01:11:31,622
I didn't have any food, any water,
and it was very cold, very cold.

897
01:11:34,291 --> 01:11:38,378
I thought if I could save just one, but,

898
01:11:40,964 --> 01:11:42,591
he was so heavy.

899
01:11:43,592 --> 01:11:45,219
He was so heavy.

900
01:11:50,474 --> 01:11:54,812
I didn't get more than a few miles
when the sheriff's car picked me up.

901
01:11:57,564 --> 01:11:58,816
The rancher was so angry,

902
01:11:58,982 --> 01:12:02,361
he sent me to live
at the Lutheran orphanage in Bozeman.

903
01:12:02,528 --> 01:12:04,696
I never saw the ranch again.

904
01:12:05,322 --> 01:12:07,783
What became of your lamb, Clarice?

905
01:12:09,993 --> 01:12:11,578
They killed him.

906
01:12:11,745 --> 01:12:14,039
You still wake up sometimes, don't you?

907
01:12:14,206 --> 01:12:18,710
Wake up in the dark
and hear the screaming of the lambs.

908
01:12:19,795 --> 01:12:20,879
Yes.

909
01:12:22,631 --> 01:12:26,885
And you think if you save poor Catherine,
you could make them stop, don't you?

910
01:12:27,052 --> 01:12:29,304
You think if Catherine lives,

911
01:12:29,471 --> 01:12:32,182
you won't wake up in the dark ever again

912
01:12:32,683 --> 01:12:35,352
to that awful screaming of the lambs.

913
01:12:36,687 --> 01:12:39,690
I don't know. I don't know.

914
01:12:41,859 --> 01:12:45,529
Thank you, Clarice. Thank you.

915
01:12:46,363 --> 01:12:48,407
Tell me his name, Doctor.

916
01:12:55,372 --> 01:12:57,291
Dr. Chilton, I presume.

917
01:12:58,166 --> 01:13:00,335
I think you know each other.

918
01:13:01,962 --> 01:13:03,255
Okay.

919
01:13:04,256 --> 01:13:06,258
- We found her.
- Let's go!

920
01:13:06,550 --> 01:13:08,468
It's your turn, Doctor.

921
01:13:08,719 --> 01:13:10,637
- Out.
- Tell me his name.

922
01:13:10,804 --> 01:13:13,432
Sorry, ma'am, I've got orders.
I have to put you on a plane.

923
01:13:13,599 --> 01:13:14,892
Come on now.

924
01:13:15,058 --> 01:13:16,560
Brave Clarice.

925
01:13:17,227 --> 01:13:20,939
You will let me know when
those lambs stop screaming, won't you?

926
01:13:21,106 --> 01:13:23,025
Tell me his name, Doctor!

927
01:13:23,191 --> 01:13:24,401
Clarice!

928
01:13:25,736 --> 01:13:27,321
Your case file.

929
01:13:32,534 --> 01:13:34,244
Goodbye, Clarice.

930
01:14:40,018 --> 01:14:42,020
Ready when you are, Doc.

931
01:14:42,229 --> 01:14:44,398
Just another minute, please.

932
01:14:53,323 --> 01:14:55,701
The son of a bitch
demanded a second dinner.

933
01:14:55,867 --> 01:14:57,828
Lamb chops, extra rare.

934
01:14:57,995 --> 01:14:59,830
Wonder what he wants for breakfast.

935
01:14:59,997 --> 01:15:02,249
Some damn thing from the zoo?

936
01:15:24,021 --> 01:15:25,772
Good evening, gentlemen.

937
01:15:25,939 --> 01:15:29,401
- Okay, Doc. Grab some floor.
- Same drill as before, please.

938
01:15:37,034 --> 01:15:39,536
Ready when you are, Sergeant Pembry.

939
01:15:55,761 --> 01:15:56,887
Okay.

940
01:16:03,769 --> 01:16:05,771
Hand me that, would you?

941
01:16:10,984 --> 01:16:12,194
Thanks.

942
01:16:16,031 --> 01:16:18,075
Mind the drawings, please.

943
01:16:21,161 --> 01:16:22,496
Thank you.

944
01:16:46,895 --> 01:16:49,189
- Jimmy, watch it! He's got me!
- Jesus, Bill!

945
01:16:56,154 --> 01:16:57,656
Jesus Christ!

946
01:18:16,276 --> 01:18:18,862
Ready when you are, Sergeant Pembry.

947
01:18:28,121 --> 01:18:29,789
What is this shit?

948
01:18:32,542 --> 01:18:36,296
- Did somebody go up on five?
- No. Nobody went up.

949
01:18:36,588 --> 01:18:38,548
Call Pembry. Ask him...

950
01:18:41,176 --> 01:18:43,887
CP, shots fired on five. Repeat.

951
01:18:44,304 --> 01:18:46,848
- Shots fired on five.
- Sergeant Tate.

952
01:18:49,559 --> 01:18:50,852
Holy shit.

953
01:18:51,019 --> 01:18:52,771
What the hell? Bitch!

954
01:18:53,355 --> 01:18:54,564
Shut up.

955
01:18:54,898 --> 01:18:57,400
- Bobby, get the vest.
- Right, Sarge.

956
01:18:58,068 --> 01:18:59,986
- Brady, Howard...
- Look!

957
01:19:03,114 --> 01:19:04,532
It stopped.

958
01:19:06,034 --> 01:19:07,661
Seal off a 10 block radius.

959
01:19:07,827 --> 01:19:10,580
Get me the SWAT team
and an ambulance double-quick.

960
01:19:10,747 --> 01:19:11,915
We're going up.

961
01:19:41,027 --> 01:19:42,612
Pembry!

962
01:19:44,114 --> 01:19:45,865
Boyle!

963
01:19:58,503 --> 01:19:59,754
Oh, God!

964
01:20:07,012 --> 01:20:08,054
Go.

965
01:20:15,854 --> 01:20:17,272
- Clear!
- Clear!

966
01:20:17,439 --> 01:20:20,358
Command post, two officers down.

967
01:20:20,775 --> 01:20:22,110
- Clear!
- Clear!

968
01:20:22,986 --> 01:20:24,321
Lecter's gone, Sarge.

969
01:20:24,487 --> 01:20:26,197
The prisoner is missing.

970
01:20:26,364 --> 01:20:28,241
Boyle's gun is gone, Sergeant.

971
01:20:28,408 --> 01:20:30,869
Repeat. Lecter is missing and armed.

972
01:20:31,036 --> 01:20:34,039
He stripped the bed.
Might be making a rope.

973
01:20:34,205 --> 01:20:35,749
Check all windows.

974
01:20:35,915 --> 01:20:38,251
Where the fuck is my ambulance?

975
01:20:38,918 --> 01:20:40,337
He's alive.

976
01:20:41,004 --> 01:20:43,089
Sergeant Tate, he's alive!

977
01:20:43,631 --> 01:20:46,718
Get ahold of him where you can
feel his hands, son. Talk to him.

978
01:20:47,260 --> 01:20:48,470
What do I say?

979
01:20:48,636 --> 01:20:51,348
It's Jim Pembry! Now talk to him, damn it!

980
01:20:52,349 --> 01:20:54,517
Lecter is missing and armed.

981
01:20:54,684 --> 01:20:56,895
Pembry. Pembry, can you hear me?

982
01:20:57,062 --> 01:20:59,981
He took Boyle's gun.
Pembry got off one round.

983
01:21:00,148 --> 01:21:02,067
There's a chance Lecter was hit.

984
01:21:02,233 --> 01:21:04,235
Keep breathing in and out. That's it.

985
01:21:04,402 --> 01:21:07,572
You're doing a good job.
You look real good there.

986
01:21:08,365 --> 01:21:11,201
Yeah, you look... You look real good.

987
01:21:28,426 --> 01:21:29,511
- You ready?
- Let's go.

988
01:21:29,677 --> 01:21:31,554
- Let's do it.
- Let's go.

989
01:21:42,607 --> 01:21:44,776
Looking good, Pembry.
You're gonna make it.

990
01:21:44,943 --> 01:21:47,088
You're just fine. You're doing all right.
That's right.

991
01:21:47,112 --> 01:21:49,447
- Okay, I need that IV now.
- Lactated ringers.

992
01:21:49,614 --> 01:21:50,782
Can we get the strap?

993
01:21:50,949 --> 01:21:52,009
Where's the fucking oxygen?

994
01:21:52,033 --> 01:21:53,713
- Looking good, buddy. That's right.
- Bob!

995
01:21:53,868 --> 01:21:55,620
Stay with me. Stay with me here.

996
01:21:57,288 --> 01:21:59,541
We're losing him. Downstairs. Take him!

997
01:22:00,333 --> 01:22:01,543
And up!

998
01:22:03,086 --> 01:22:04,206
- Elevator!
- Out of the way!

999
01:22:04,337 --> 01:22:05,839
Out of the way!

1000
01:22:10,635 --> 01:22:12,011
<i>CP to Tate.</i>

1001
01:22:12,720 --> 01:22:14,931
Roger, Lieutenant. Tate here.

1002
01:22:15,598 --> 01:22:18,435
I'm on the elevator bringing Pembry down.

1003
01:22:18,726 --> 01:22:20,770
He seems to be hanging on.

1004
01:22:21,396 --> 01:22:23,398
Top three floors secured.

1005
01:22:24,023 --> 01:22:25,942
Main stairwell secured.

1006
01:22:26,985 --> 01:22:28,778
We think he's on two.

1007
01:22:42,125 --> 01:22:44,252
<i>Tate, are you still with me?</i>

1008
01:22:46,212 --> 01:22:48,590
We're pretty sure
he's somewhere on two, sir.

1009
01:22:48,756 --> 01:22:50,675
That's all for now. Over.

1010
01:23:10,153 --> 01:23:12,572
He's on the roof of the elevator.

1011
01:23:15,325 --> 01:23:16,743
Okay, guys.

1012
01:23:33,343 --> 01:23:34,677
I see him.

1013
01:23:34,844 --> 01:23:37,680
There's a gun by his hand.
He's not moving.

1014
01:23:38,014 --> 01:23:39,807
One warning. We need him alive.

1015
01:23:39,974 --> 01:23:41,267
<i>Got him.</i>

1016
01:23:41,851 --> 01:23:43,102
Lecter.

1017
01:23:43,520 --> 01:23:45,688
Put your hands on your head.

1018
01:23:47,774 --> 01:23:49,317
One in the leg.

1019
01:24:00,328 --> 01:24:01,704
No movement.

1020
01:24:03,039 --> 01:24:06,084
Johnny, hold your fire.
We're coming into the car.

1021
01:24:06,251 --> 01:24:09,462
- We're opening the hatch.
- Watch his hands.

1022
01:24:09,629 --> 01:24:12,799
If there's any fire,
it'll come from us. Affirm.

1023
01:24:13,007 --> 01:24:14,217
<i>Got it.</i>

1024
01:24:40,201 --> 01:24:42,203
Memphis General, this is Medical Unit 26.

1025
01:24:42,370 --> 01:24:44,872
We're inbound with a 50-year-old
male police officer

1026
01:24:45,039 --> 01:24:47,375
with severe facial lacerations.
Weapon unknown.

1027
01:24:47,542 --> 01:24:50,461
We've got grand mal seizure activity,
but he's postictal now.

1028
01:24:50,628 --> 01:24:51,588
<i>Copy that.</i>

1029
01:24:51,754 --> 01:24:54,549
Vital signs are good.
Pressure is 130 over 90.

1030
01:24:54,716 --> 01:24:56,134
<i>- Ninety?</i>
- Yeah, that's right. 90.

1031
01:24:56,301 --> 01:24:57,468
Pulse, 84.

1032
01:24:57,635 --> 01:24:59,315
We've got him on lactated ringers running.

1033
01:24:59,345 --> 01:25:01,889
And the patient is on 10 liters...

1034
01:25:09,063 --> 01:25:12,317
They found the ambulance
in a parking garage at Memphis Airport.

1035
01:25:12,483 --> 01:25:13,943
The crew was dead.

1036
01:25:15,028 --> 01:25:18,531
He killed a tourist, too.
Got his clothes, cash.

1037
01:25:19,115 --> 01:25:21,075
By now he could be anywhere.

1038
01:25:21,242 --> 01:25:23,161
- He won't come after me.
- Oh, really?

1039
01:25:23,328 --> 01:25:25,705
No, he won't. I can't explain it.

1040
01:25:25,872 --> 01:25:28,458
He would consider that rude.

1041
01:25:29,626 --> 01:25:31,502
It's over. She's dead.

1042
01:25:31,753 --> 01:25:33,588
It's not your fault it
worked out like this.

1043
01:25:33,755 --> 01:25:35,608
The thing is that,
Lecter said everything we need

1044
01:25:35,632 --> 01:25:38,112
to catch him with is right here
in these pages, only I can't...

1045
01:25:38,259 --> 01:25:41,971
- Dr. Lecter said a lot of things.
- He's here, Ardelia.

1046
01:26:11,793 --> 01:26:13,378
Is this Lecter's handwriting?

1047
01:26:15,588 --> 01:26:18,216
"Clarice, doesn't this random scattering
of sites

1048
01:26:18,383 --> 01:26:22,345
"seem desperately random?
Like the elaboration of a bad liar.

1049
01:26:22,637 --> 01:26:24,222
"Ta, Hannibal Lecter."

1050
01:26:24,389 --> 01:26:27,016
Desperately random? What does he mean?

1051
01:26:27,183 --> 01:26:30,269
Not random at all maybe.
Like there's some pattern here.

1052
01:26:31,688 --> 01:26:34,899
Yeah, but there is no pattern,
or the computers would have nailed it.

1053
01:26:35,066 --> 01:26:36,859
They're even found in random order.

1054
01:26:37,443 --> 01:26:41,030
Random because of the one girl.
The one he weighted down.

1055
01:26:41,906 --> 01:26:43,658
- Fredrica Bimmel...
- Right.

1056
01:26:43,825 --> 01:26:47,036
From Belvedere, Ohio.

1057
01:26:47,537 --> 01:26:51,124
First girl taken, third body found. Why?

1058
01:26:51,290 --> 01:26:53,584
Well, she didn't drift.
He weighted her down.

1059
01:26:53,751 --> 01:26:56,754
What did Lecter say
about the first principles?

1060
01:26:57,171 --> 01:26:58,548
Simplicity.

1061
01:26:58,923 --> 01:27:01,467
What does this guy do? He covets.

1062
01:27:02,385 --> 01:27:04,721
How do we first start to covet?

1063
01:27:05,346 --> 01:27:07,974
- We covet what we see...
- Every day.

1064
01:27:10,601 --> 01:27:13,104
- Hot damn, Clarice.
- He knew her.

1065
01:28:29,013 --> 01:28:31,182
- Mr. Bimmel?
- That's me.

1066
01:28:32,225 --> 01:28:35,061
Hello. I'm Clarice Starling.
I'm with the FBI.

1067
01:28:38,606 --> 01:28:41,776
I sure appreciate you letting me
take a look around, Mr. Bimmel.

1068
01:28:42,485 --> 01:28:44,695
I don't know nothing new to tell you.

1069
01:28:44,862 --> 01:28:48,032
Police been back here
so many times already.

1070
01:28:48,449 --> 01:28:51,994
Fredrica went into Chicago on the bus
to see about a job.

1071
01:28:52,745 --> 01:28:55,915
She left the interview okay.
She never come home.

1072
01:28:59,085 --> 01:29:01,337
Her bedroom's how she left it.

1073
01:29:01,671 --> 01:29:04,257
Upstairs. Door to the left.

1074
01:31:50,006 --> 01:31:53,175
<i>He's making himself a woman suit,
Mr. Crawford, out of real women.</i>

1075
01:31:53,342 --> 01:31:56,220
And he can sew, this guy.
He's very skilled.

1076
01:31:56,387 --> 01:31:58,723
- He's a tailor or a dressmaker or...
<i>- Starling...</i>

1077
01:31:58,889 --> 01:32:01,267
That's why they're all so big.
He has to keep them alive

1078
01:32:01,434 --> 01:32:02,577
so he can starve them a while,

1079
01:32:02,601 --> 01:32:04,538
- so he can loosen their skin and take...
<i>- Starling.</i>

1080
01:32:04,562 --> 01:32:07,023
<i>Starling. Starling,
we know who he is and where he is.</i>

1081
01:32:07,189 --> 01:32:09,400
<i>- We're on our way right now.
- Where?</i>

1082
01:32:09,692 --> 01:32:14,321
Calumet City, edge of Chicago.
Be on the ground in 45 minutes with HRT.

1083
01:32:14,488 --> 01:32:16,782
Oh, that's great news, sir, but how...

1084
01:32:16,949 --> 01:32:18,868
<i>Johns Hopkins came up with some names.</i>

1085
01:32:18,993 --> 01:32:20,453
<i>We fed him into "Known Offenders."</i>

1086
01:32:20,619 --> 01:32:24,707
Subject's name is Jamie Gumb,
AKA John Grant.

1087
01:32:24,874 --> 01:32:27,314
<i>Lecter's description is accurate.
He just lied about the name.</i>

1088
01:32:27,418 --> 01:32:28,461
<i>Listen to this.</i>

1089
01:32:28,669 --> 01:32:30,880
Customs had some paper on him.

1090
01:32:31,130 --> 01:32:34,050
They stopped a carton two years ago
at LAX.

1091
01:32:34,300 --> 01:32:36,552
Live caterpillars from Surinam.

1092
01:32:36,719 --> 01:32:39,221
The addressee was a Jame Gumb.

1093
01:32:40,181 --> 01:32:42,099
Well, Chicago's only 400 miles from here.

1094
01:32:42,266 --> 01:32:44,026
- I'll be there in...
<i>- No, no, no, Starling.</i>

1095
01:32:44,185 --> 01:32:47,396
There's not enough time.
We want him for murder, not kidnapping.

1096
01:32:47,563 --> 01:32:50,043
I need you to link him to the Bimmel girl
before he's indicted.

1097
01:32:50,107 --> 01:32:54,111
- See what you can dredge up in Belvedere.
- Yes, sir. You bet. I'll do my best.

1098
01:32:54,278 --> 01:32:57,531
Starling, we wouldn't have found him
without you.

1099
01:32:58,074 --> 01:33:01,410
Nobody's gonna forget that.
Least of all me.

1100
01:33:02,953 --> 01:33:06,165
Thank you, sir.
Thank you very much, Mr. Crawford.

1101
01:33:07,917 --> 01:33:09,335
Mr. Crawford?

1102
01:33:21,931 --> 01:33:25,851
Thanks for the scraps, asshole.
I got a better idea.

1103
01:33:47,790 --> 01:33:50,209
Okay, Precious. Time for a little treat.

1104
01:34:03,305 --> 01:34:04,640
Precious!

1105
01:34:07,184 --> 01:34:08,686
Come on, girl!

1106
01:34:09,937 --> 01:34:12,523
Come on, Precious. Come on, Precious!

1107
01:34:21,657 --> 01:34:23,367
Come on, Precious!

1108
01:34:23,659 --> 01:34:26,203
I got a yummy, yummy snack for you.

1109
01:34:26,537 --> 01:34:27,997
Come on. Come and get it.

1110
01:34:34,962 --> 01:34:36,255
Precious!

1111
01:34:37,173 --> 01:34:39,633
Are you up there, you little shit?

1112
01:34:40,509 --> 01:34:42,720
Come and get it, pretty girl.

1113
01:34:49,852 --> 01:34:53,397
Precious. Please come. Come on.

1114
01:35:01,363 --> 01:35:02,823
Come on...

1115
01:35:15,211 --> 01:35:16,879
Would you fuck me?

1116
01:35:17,129 --> 01:35:19,548
Come on. Take that bone. Come on.

1117
01:35:20,799 --> 01:35:23,552
Come on. Come. Come on.

1118
01:35:23,969 --> 01:35:25,387
I'd fuck me.

1119
01:35:26,013 --> 01:35:27,264
Come on.

1120
01:35:31,310 --> 01:35:33,020
I'd fuck me hard.

1121
01:35:33,437 --> 01:35:35,272
I'd fuck me so hard.

1122
01:35:40,194 --> 01:35:41,237
No.

1123
01:36:42,381 --> 01:36:44,508
Is that a good job, FBI agent?

1124
01:36:44,675 --> 01:36:48,804
You get to travel around and stuff?
I mean, better places than this?

1125
01:36:50,472 --> 01:36:52,099
Sometimes you do.

1126
01:36:52,933 --> 01:36:56,645
Freddie was so happy for me
when I got this job at the bank.

1127
01:36:57,438 --> 01:37:01,191
Toaster giveaways and Barry Manilow
on the speakers all day.

1128
01:37:01,483 --> 01:37:03,902
She thought it was such hot shit.

1129
01:37:04,486 --> 01:37:06,739
What did she know? Big dummy.

1130
01:37:06,989 --> 01:37:09,241
Stacy, did Fredrica ever mention a man

1131
01:37:09,408 --> 01:37:12,995
named Jamie Gumb or a Jame Gumb?

1132
01:37:13,829 --> 01:37:15,873
- How about John Grant?
- No.

1133
01:37:16,332 --> 01:37:17,392
Oh, would she have had a friend

1134
01:37:17,416 --> 01:37:18,685
that you didn't know about, or...

1135
01:37:18,709 --> 01:37:21,462
No way. If she had a guy, I'd have known,
believe me.

1136
01:37:21,628 --> 01:37:23,339
Sewing was her life.

1137
01:37:23,922 --> 01:37:25,716
Did you two ever work together?

1138
01:37:25,883 --> 01:37:27,801
Oh, sure. Me and Pam Malavesi
used to help her

1139
01:37:27,968 --> 01:37:30,471
do alterations for old Mrs. Lippman.

1140
01:37:30,929 --> 01:37:33,891
Can you give me Mrs. Lippman's address?
I need to talk to her.

1141
01:38:02,628 --> 01:38:05,631
So powerful. So beautiful.

1142
01:38:11,220 --> 01:38:12,513
Precious?

1143
01:38:18,435 --> 01:38:19,478
Precious?

1144
01:38:19,645 --> 01:38:21,814
Down here, you sack of shit!

1145
01:38:30,656 --> 01:38:31,698
Put her in that bucket.

1146
01:38:31,865 --> 01:38:35,369
No! You get me a telephone
and lower it down here. Now!

1147
01:38:38,080 --> 01:38:40,457
Poolie-poo. Precious.

1148
01:38:40,749 --> 01:38:42,376
Darling heart, are you all right?

1149
01:38:42,543 --> 01:38:45,629
She's in a lot of pain, mister.
She needs a vet.

1150
01:38:49,716 --> 01:38:52,594
She broke her leg on the way down.
I know it. She's been licking...

1151
